


Write a function that takes any non-negative integer as an argument and returns its digits rearranged in descending order. Essentially, rearrange the digits to form the largest possible number.



public class DescendingOrder {
    public static int sortDigitsDescending(int number) {
        // Convert the number to a string and then to a character array
        char[] digits = Integer.toString(number).toCharArray();

        // Sort the character array in descending order
        Arrays.sort(digits);

        // Reverse the sorted array
        StringBuilder reversed = new StringBuilder(new String(digits)).reverse();

        // Convert the result back to an integer
        return Integer.parseInt(reversed.toString());
    }
